CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "Nation-Wide Delegation-Among the delegates from nation-wide cities who attended the meeting of Prince Hall Masons this week at the Hotel Fort Pitt are, seated: O.C. Abernathy and Clyde S. Lange, who became a 33 degree Mason, both of Denver, Colo., and,. standing, left to right: George Ellis, of Dayton, Ohio; Fred W. Hickman, of Milwaukee; Wade McCurley, of Kansas City, Kans., and S.A. Moss, of Seattle, Wash."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of 33 degree Masons, seated: O.C. Abernathy and Clyde S. Lange; standing from left: George Ellis, Fred W. Hickman, Wade McCurley, and S.A. Moss, gathered around small sofa in the Fort Pitt Hotel for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33 Degree Masons
